akota%20Rae%20Lowe's%20separation%20from%20her%20recent%20ex%20was%20messy%2C%20and%20the%20drama%20spilled%20out%20onto%20LinkedIn%2C%20where%20both%20have%20formidable%20presences.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-cringe-how-to-post-new-job-hiring-resume-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eposted%20a%20mirror%20selfie%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20platform%2C%20and%20she%2C%20finding%20it%20cringy%2C%20posted%20a%20subtweet%20about%20it%2C%20saying%20if%20she%20ever%20did%20the%20same%2C%20%26quot%3Bplease%20report%20me.%26quot%3B%20Lowe%2C%2030%2C%20who%20works%20in%20advertising%20in%20New%20York%2C%20still%20catches%20her%20ex%20%26quot%3Bshamelessly%20viewing%26quot%3B%20her%20profile%2C%20even%20though%20they%20split%20months%20ago.%20%26quot%3BCan%20he%20not%20afford%20Premium%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20paid%20invisible-browsing%20tier.%20%26quot%3BI%20pay%20for%20Premium%2C%20because%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20be%20embarrassed%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20have%20had%20similar%20experiences.%20When%20a%20short-lived%20relationship%20petered%20out%20in%202022%2C%20Kevin%20Grunewald%2C%20now%2040%2C%20thought%20things%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flessons-learned-breakups-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eended%20on%20relatively%20amicable%20terms%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20relationships%2C%20it%20didn't%20quite%20work.%20But%20then%20the%20Texas-based%20recruiter%20noticed%20the%20woman%20he'd%20dated%20was%20viewing%20his%20LinkedIn%20profile%20almost%20daily%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20was%20part%20of%20her%20morning%20ritual%2C%20I%20guess%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20She%20began%20liking%20his%20posts%20and%20messaging%20him%2C%20and%20he%20finally%20had%20to%20put%20his%20foot%20down%20after%20she%20popped%20by%20his%20house%20a%20few%20times%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20she%20blocked%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20I'm%20kind%20of%20happy%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGina%20Gacad%2C%20a%2031-year-old%20communications%20professional%20in%20New%20York%2C%20noticed%20the%20mother%20of%20her%20college%20boyfriend%20lurking%20on%20her%20profile%20years%20after%20they%20broke%20up%20%E2%80%94%20and%20around%20the%20time%20she'd%20heard%20he%20was%20seeing%20someone%20new.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20wonder%20if%20they%20were%20trying%20to%20size%20up%20the%20new%20girlfriend%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20(A%20running%20theme%20in%20my%20conversations%20was%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-post-help-family-job-search-risks-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eparents%20are%20often%20the%20problem%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Less%20digitally%20savvy%20%E2%80%94%20and%20digitally%20bashful%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20the%20ones%20searching%20without%20abandon%20on%20LinkedIn.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20Gacad%20isn't%20above%20some%20LinkedIn%20prowling%20of%20her%20own.%20Another%20ex%20belittled%20her%20about%20her%20job%2C%20and%20when%20his%20employer%20had%20layoffs%2C%20she%20went%20to%20his%20LinkedIn%20to%20see%20if%20he%20was%20on%20the%20chopping%20block.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20let%20go%2C%20which%20was%20unfortunate%2C%20but%20also%20he%20was%20being%20a%20dick%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20She's%20not%20worried%20about%20former%20paramours%20returning%20the%20favor%2C%20either.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20when%20a%20guy%20would%20wrong%20me%2C%20or%20someone%20would%20wrong%20me%2C%20LinkedIn%20was%20the%20place%20where%20I%20would%20validate%20myself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20recurring%20theme%20among%20the%20people%20I%20spoke%20to%3A%20Not%20everyone%20is%20taken%20aback%20to%20see%20someone%20from%20the%20past%20poking%20around%20in%20their%20business-related%20business.%20Many%20are%20proud%20of%20their%20professional%20accomplishments%2C%20and%20they're%20happy%20for%20others%20to%20see%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20people%2C%20LinkedIn%20lurking%20doesn't%20just%20feel%20awkward%20or%20validating%20%E2%80%94%20it%20feels%20threatening.%20People%20often%20share%20a%20lot%20of%20specific%20information%20about%20themselves%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20including%20their%20location%20and%20workplace.%20LinkedIn%20comes%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-open-to-work-banner-badge-job-pros-cons-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20privacy%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20some%20people%20may%20not%20want%20to%20pay.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20being%20invisible%20may%20come%20with%20another%20tax%20%E2%80%94%20lost%20job%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20she%20moved%20to%20Spain%20in%202023%2C%20Amanda%20Brooks%2C%2030%2C%20met%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhinge-success-match-group-tinder-ceo-spencer-rascoff-dating-apps-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eguy%20on%20Hinge%3C%2Fa%3E%20whom%20she%20quickly%20realized%20wasn't%20right%20for%20her.%20She%20blocked%20him%20on%20social%20media%20after%20he%20wouldn't%20take%20no%20for%20an%20answer%20to%20his%20request%20for%20a%20second%20date.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20he%20followed%20her%20on%20LinkedIn%20and%20began%20liking%20her%20posts%20and%20regularly%20checking%20her%20profile.%20So%20she%20blocked%20him%20there%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BCrazy%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20She's%20not%20super%20worried%20about%20the%20man%20anymore%2C%20but%20it%20has%20made%20her%20rethink%20her%20approach%20to%20the%20internet%2C%20including%20LinkedIn.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20kind%20of%20get%20comfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERT%2C%20whom%20I%20agreed%20to%20grant%20anonymity%20for%20this%20story%20to%20protect%20her%20privacy%2C%20can't%20seem%20to%20shake%20her%20former%20partner's%20shadow.%20They%20ended%20things%20in%202020%2C%20after%20which%20he%20haunted%20her%20for%20a%20year%2C%20including%20waiting%20outside%20her%20home%20and%20confronting%20her%20father%20at%20his%20workplace.%20He%20also%20threatened%20to%20call%20her%20employer%20and%20have%20her%20fired%20for%20smoking%20marijuana.%20RT%2C%20who%20is%20in%20her%2030s%2C%20is%20now%20happily%20married%20and%20lives%20abroad%2C%20but%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20ago%2C%20she%20noticed%20her%20ex's%20father%20was%20looking%20at%20her%20LinkedIn%20profile.%20%26quot%3BHis%20dad%20is%20retired%2C%20so%20there's%20not%20really%20a%20reason%20for%20him%20to%20be%20on%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20blocked%20her%20ex%20everywhere%2C%20lives%20thousands%20of%20miles%20away%2C%20and%20still%2C%20the%20concern%20about%20what%20he%20might%20see%20holds%20her%20back%2C%20which%20is%20especially%20detrimental%20given%20that%20she's%20a%20corporate%20recruiter.%20%26quot%3BIt%20does%20have%20me%20kind%20of%20wary%20of%20posting%20on%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BWho%20knows%20what%20other%20family%20members%20might%20try%20to%20look%3F%20Or%20other%20people%20he%20might%20know%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDA%2C%20who%20I%20also%20granted%20anonymity%2C%20echoes%20the%20sentiment.%20She's%20currently%20on%20the%20job%20market%20and%20wonders%20if%20limiting%20the%20information%20on%20her%20LinkedIn%20profile%20to%20avoid%20an%20ex's%20surveillance%20will%20hurt%20her%20prospects.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20this%20huge%20push%20for%20people%20to%20be%20LinkedIn%20influencers%20and%20everything%20to%20be%20noticed%20by%20employers%2C%20and%20that's%20been%20really%20hard%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20like%20I'm%20afraid%20of%20being%20judged%20for%20putting%20myself%20out%20there%2C%20I'm%20afraid%20of%20being%20stalked%20and%20this%20guy%20having%20too%20much%20information.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20LinkedIn%20user%2C%20you%20may%20h