Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20the%20possibility%20of%20an%20emotional%20setback%20is%20enough%20to%20keep%20them%20away.%20Holly%20Benjamin%2C%20a%2032-year-old%20marketer%20from%20Boston%2C%20recently%20considered%20looking%20up%20an%20ex%20from%20over%20a%20decade%20ago%20on%20LinkedIn.%20Things%20ended%20poorly%20%E2%80%94%20with%20a%20restraining%20order%20%E2%80%94%20and%20she's%20worried%20that%20if%20she%20does%20take%20a%20look%20and%20he%20looks%20in%20return%2C%20it%20could%20send%20her%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Byearlong%20spiral.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20natural%20to%20be%20curious%20about%20where%20people%20ended%20up%2C%20but%20LinkedIn%20is%20the%20only%20platform%20where%20that%20curiosity%20can%20feel%20a%20little%20risky%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BA%20neutral%20action%20becomes%20something%20that%20has%20a%20lot%20more%20thought%20behind%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20LinkedIn%20former%20lover%20stakeouts%20have%20a%20bad%20ending%20%E2%80%94%20indeed%2C%20it%20can%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-is-a-dating-app-remote-work-online-romance-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Equite%20the%20opposite%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20what%20happened%20to%20Lisette%20Hall%2C%20a%2042-year-old%20marketer%20in%20Chicago.%20In%202023%2C%20a%20man%20she'd%20known%20from%20high%20school%20added%20her%20on%20LinkedIn%3B%20they%20hadn't%20spoken%20in%2020%20years.%20When%20she%20brought%20it%20up%20to%20friends%2C%20some%20of%20them%20told%20her%20to%20ignore%20it.%20It%20was%20an%20unusual%20move%2C%20after%20all%2C%20and%20he%20hadn't%20sent%20a%20message.%20But%20she%20went%20ahead%20and%20accepted%20the%20request%2C%20since%20they'd%20had%20crushes%20on%20each%20other%20way%20back%20when.%20After%20that%2C%20they%20got%20to%20chatting.%20They're%20now%20married.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20points%20out%20that%20he%20could%20have%20just%20Googled%20her%2C%20especially%20since%20she%20has%20a%20website%20where%20he%20could%20have%20contacted%20her.%20He%20thought%20LinkedIn%20would%20be%20the%20least%20creepy%20avenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-love-people-stalking-exes-screening-dates-job-market-careers-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1768209421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F696161c704eda4732f2ed227%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-love-people-stalking-exes-screening-dates-job-market-careers-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22LinkedIn%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20place%20to%20find%20a%20job.%20But%20people%20are%20using%20the%20social%20media%20app%20to%20look%20up%20exes%20and%20screen%20potential%20romantic%20interests.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-love-people-stalking-exes-screening-dates-job-market-careers-2026-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We%20asked%20over%20150%20software%20engineers%20about%20vibe-coding.%20Here's%20what%20they%20said.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Javanie%20Campbell%2C%20Gus%20De%20Souza%2C%20and%20Shawn%20Gay%20are%20pictured.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69601f7d04eda4732f2ebe6f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJavanie%20Campbell%2C%20Gus%20De%20Souza%2C%20and%20Shawn%